Text:
After receiving a passionate lecture from the branch
manager about the essence of customer service, Delta
and Eta’s next course of action is—

The pumpkin pies taste different at different food
stalls! Some are sweet, and others are stuffed with
meat!

Lazing around in the hustle and bustle...is kinda
nice...
You eat too, Eta!
Mmph... Don't...force me...

Despite the branch manager's fervent speech, the two
continue enjoying Halloween without a care in the
world.
*sigh*
What's with the sigh? Aren't you gonna eat too?

Skewered chicken... I'm not in the mood to enjoy a
meal right now. Can't you two understand what I'm
trying to convey?
...Business is booming.
BEEP BEEP...BEEP...
...It'll reach its quota soon.
Huh?
...The sweets in Mr. Vendy are about to run out...

Oh, it's done already? Well, I'll head back to the
stalls then!
...I'm going home...

Ohh... Is it going to end like this? Mitsugoshi's
principles won't be properly conveyed to our
customers...

As the branch manager laments, a boy rushes up to
Mr. Vendy.
Trick or treat!
BEEP BEEP...BEEP... PSHHHT... OUT OF STOCK...
Oh... It's done.

It's run out of stock. Alright, I'll give that boy
his sweets, and we can wrap up this event—

But as the branch manager tries to approach the
boy...
Mr. Vendy's suddenly got...a different smell.
Huh?
OUT OF STOCK... RESTOCKING.

Mr. Vendy blares an error message, and its built-in
arms and legs start to move, snatching sweets from
children nearby.
Eeeek!
Wha—?! What's going on?!
It's rampaging.

Now isn't the time for such calm remarks! If we don't
hurry up and stop it, the children might get hurt!
...Go on, Delta...
Jeez, fine. Be right back!
RESTOCKING... RESTOCKING...
Stop right there!

Delta leaps forward and kicks Mr. Vendy's extended
arm away from a girl holding sweets.
The crowd is kind of getting in Delta's way...
Ah! Everyone, please step back!

Mitsugoshi employees from the branch rush over,
guiding the public away from the scene.

Delta confronts Mr. Vendy head-on. Sensing this is no
time to be lazing around, Eta joins her.

Eta, what's going on? Why's Mr. Vendy acting so
weird?

...Well, I made it in a hurry, so the restocking
system is a bit sloppy...
...What's that supposed to mean?

It's an automated system for restocking sweets. But
the settings for where it restocks from... Well, you
get the picture.
I don't really get it!
...If you don't get it, that's fine.
Mr. Vendy is rampaging. Stop him.
I see! That's simple and easy to get!

With a wild grin on her face, Delta charges straight
at Mr. Vendy...
Wha—?!

BEEP BEEP.. LOOTER IDENTIFIED. INITIATING
ELIMINATION PROTOCOL.

Mr. Vendy's arms and legs move swiftly, launching an
attack in an attempt to eliminate Delta.
Eta?! What the heck is this?!

...I thought enemies might come to steal the sweets,
so I equipped it with an armed security system...
...It's the perfect security system.
Security...system?

But it's only natural to protect food from enemies!
Well done, Eta!

This isn't a time for compliments! Why did you focus
on those features and neglect the restocking system?
...Personal tastes...?

Personal tastes...? Oh, Lady Delta! It's stealing
your food!
What'd you say?!

Delta turns around, only to find Mr. Vendy's extended
arms snatching the snacks and food she had procured.
Boss man's souvenirs...! I won't let you take 'em!
Eta! How do we stop Mr. Vendy?!

...There's an emergency shutdown switch. But it'll be
tough to press it while it's rampaging...

Then I'll make it stop moving! You do something in
the meantime!
...Talk about unscheduled labor...
Alright, here goes!

While Mr. Vendy continues its rampage, Delta
fearlessly leaps toward it. Eta looks for her
opening...
